***Version [0.31](/0.31 "0.31")**: This article **may not be** up to date for the [latest stable release](/0.32 "0.32") of Crawl.*

An **unrand** (or **unrandart**) is short for **"unrandom artefact,"** an [artefact](/Artefact "Artefact") with set appearance and properties. Unrands are always the same between games, as opposed to [randarts](/Randart "Randart") ("random artefacts", which have randomly generated properties). Unrands may have special mechanics not found anywhere else in the game, such as the [Rift](/Rift "Rift")'s ability to attack 3 tiles away. Unrands with unique properties have historically been called **fixedarts**, though the distinction has become increasingly blurred with time.

Only one instance of any particular unrand may generate per game.

- If you don't pick up an unrand that generates in a temporary [portal](/Portal "Portal") level, or accidentally destroy the unrand by dumping it into [lava](/Lava "Lava"), it is lost forever.
- Any unrand in the possession of a monster you [banish](/Banish "Banish") to the [Abyss](/Abyss "Abyss") can be found in the Abyss, though this may take a very, very long time.
- If an [acquirement](/Acquirement "Acquirement") (either from a [scroll](/Scroll_of_acquirement "Scroll of acquirement") or an [Okawaru](/Okawaru "Okawaru") gift) offers an unrand and you pick something else, it can generate elsewhere.

Although you are almost guaranteed to find at least one unrand over the course of any given game, there is no guarantee that any particular unrand will generate, or that the unrands that *do* generate will be of any use to you.

Certain unrands are more likely to spawn in the early game, where they are most useful:[\[1\]](#cite_note-1) [Delatra's gloves](/Delatra%27s_gloves "Delatra's gloves"), [woodcutter's axe](/Woodcutter%27s_axe "Woodcutter's axe"), [Throatcutter](/Throatcutter "Throatcutter"), [Hermit's pendant](/Hermit%27s_pendant "Hermit's pendant"), [Devastator](/Devastator "Devastator"), [ratskin cloak](/Ratskin_cloak "Ratskin cloak"), [Kryia's mail coat](/Kryia%27s_mail_coat "Kryia's mail coat"), [Lear's hauberk](/Lear%27s_hauberk "Lear's hauberk"), [trident of the Octopus King](/Trident_of_the_Octopus_King "Trident of the Octopus King"), [robe of Augmentation](/Robe_of_Augmentation "Robe of Augmentation"), [staff of the Meek](/Staff_of_the_Meek "Staff of the Meek"), [amulet of Elemental Vulnerability](/Amulet_of_Elemental_Vulnerability "Amulet of Elemental Vulnerability"), [robe of Misfortune](/Robe_of_Misfortune "Robe of Misfortune"), [Force Lance](/Force_Lance_\(unrand\) "Force Lance (unrand)"), and toga "[Victory](/Victory "Victory")".

